<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="mathml.xsl"?><html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:pref="http://www.w3.org/2002/Math/preference" pref:renderer="mathplayer-dl"><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" /><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="opengl-man.css" /><title>groupMemoryBarrier - OpenGL Shading Language (GLSL)</title><meta name="generator" content="DocBook XSL Stylesheets V1.69.1" /></head><body><div class="refentry" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="groupMemoryBarrier"></a><div class="titlepage"></div><div class="refnamediv"><h2>Name</h2><p>groupMemoryBarrier — controls the ordering of memory transaction issued shader invocation relative to a work group</p></div><div class="refsynopsisdiv"><h2>Declaration</h2><div class="funcsynopsis"><p><code class="funcdef">void <b class="fsfunc">groupMemoryBarrier</b>(</code>void<code>)</code>;</p></div></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="description"></a><h2>Description</h2><p>
            <code class="function">groupMemoryBarrier</code> waits on the completion of all memory accesses performed
            by an invocation of a compute shader relative to the same access performed by other invocations
            in the same work group and then returns with no other effect.
